        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-01-07T01:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-01-07T01:25:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>37. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d37fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1967–69,
                        DEF 19-6 US-JORDAN. Secret; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_HRB1"
                            >Houghton</persName> on January 2; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BLD1"
                            >Battle</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WPC1">Paul C.
                            Warnke</persName>, Counselor of the Department Robert R. Bowie, and
                        Wotring at the White House; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RD1"
                            >Rusk</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-01-07T06:25:00+00:00">January 7, 1968,
                        0625Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94729. Ref: Amman’s 2831.<note n="2" xml:id="d37fn2">See <ref target="#d29fn3"
                            >footnote 3, Document 29</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>President has requested following oral message be passed to King
                            <persName>Hussein</persName> in reply King’s message of December
                        30:</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>“I appreciate the assurances you have given me in your oral message of
                            December 30 with regard to Jordanian procurement of arms from the Soviet
                            Bloc. On our part, we are prepared in principle to resume arms shipments
                            to Jordan and would begin with the following items from the priority
                            requirement list which General <persName corresp="#p_KGA1"
                                >Khammash</persName> gave to Colonel Jordan in London August 1967: <list>
                                <item>106 mm rifles</item>
                                <item>2-1/2-ton trucks</item>
                                <item>communications equipment</item>
                                <item>aerial target drone systems</item>
                                <item>ammunition</item>
                                <item>and spare parts for previously delivered US equipment.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>We welcome General <persName corresp="#p_KGA1">Khammash</persName>’s
                            contemplated visit to Washington and would expect to discuss with him
                            details (including quantities) of the above shipments and various
                            aspects of the arms question in general. We would hope that he might
                            arrive in Washington around January 10.”</p>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. We would resume arms shipments to
                        Jordan with the $6.5 million package contained in Amman’s 2396.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d37fn3">Telegram 2396 from Amman, November 27, 1967, transmitted
                            eight categories of priority requests for military equipment from a list
                            prepared by General <persName corresp="#p_KGA1">Khammash</persName>.
                            (National Archives and Records Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1"
                                >RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1967–69, DEF 12-5 JORDAN)</note> End
                            <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
